President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Donald Ray Tapia of Arizona as the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to Jamaica. Tapia is the former Chairman and CEO of Essco Group Management, the largest Hispanic owned business in Arizona. He has also been involved in various philanthropic efforts, serving on the boards of organizations such as the Sun Angel Foundation and Endowment at Arizona State University, the Tau Kappa Epsilon Educational Foundation Board, and the Boys and Girls Club of Metropolitan Phoenix. Tapia is a U.S. Army veteran and holds a B.A. and M.B.A. from Saint Leo University, where he was later awarded an Honorary Doctor of Humane Letters.